{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about","content_id":"5f5a1d52-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","description":"The Ministry of Justice is a major government department, at the heart of the justice system. We work to protect and advance the principles of justice. Our vision is to deliver a world-class justice system that works for everyone in society. ","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"responsibilities\">Responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>We are responsible for these parts of the justice system:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Courts</li>\n  <li>Prisons</li>\n  <li>Probation services</li>\n  <li>Attendance centres</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The organisation works together and with other government departments and agencies to bring the principles of justice to life for everyone in society. From our civil courts, tribunals and family law hearings, to criminal justice, prison and probation services. We work to ensure that sentences are served and offenders are encouraged to turn their lives around and become law-abiding citizens. We believe the principles of justice are pivotal and we are steadfast in our shared commitment to uphold them.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>Each year, millions of people use our services across the UK - including at over 300 courts and hearing centres, and over 100 prisons in England and Wales. We work with many other government agencies, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Children and Family Court Advisory and Support Service</li>\n  <li>Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority</li>\n  <li>HM Courts and Tribunals Service</li>\n  <li>HM Prison and Probation Service</li>\n  <li>Legal Aid Agency</li>\n  <li>Office of the Public Guardian</li>\n  <li>Youth Justice Board</li>\n</ul>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"Priorities removed due to change in leadership. Will be updated in the coming weeks","public_timestamp":"2024-07-16T08:26:16Z"},{"note":"Our priorities updated.","public_timestamp":"2022-02-28T09:16:15Z"},{"note":"The latest departmental priorities added.","public_timestamp":"2016-03-22T14:15:43Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2014-03-17T11:15:42Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":[{"title":"Our organisation chart","url":"https://data.gov.uk/dataset/a90a9f70-e28c-4a95-a7a7-f79d12fbe219/organogram-of-staff-roles-salaries"},"5b8e00ed-bc65-4559-84ef-32c61a8a9d8b","5f559714-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","241efb88-7259-40a5-9978-beb4a625a27e","3b89c43e-e830-4d7c-9742-f0a5492bdeeb","a820d301-781f-406d-9d80-dcfe820cfc2c","ad4c31d0-ada7-4074-84a1-0869cc0d9034","5f559a4b-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","5f559760-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef"],"name":"Access our information"},{"contents":["5f5595b0-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","5f559922-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef",{"title":"Jobs","url":"https://jobs.justice.gov.uk/"}],"name":"Jobs and contracts"}],"headers":[{"id":"responsibilities","level":2,"text":"Responsibilities"},{"id":"who-we-are","level":2,"text":"Who we are"}],"organisation":"dcc907d6-433c-42df-9ffb-d9c68be5dc4d","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"about","first_published_at":"2014-03-17T11:15:42+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about.cy","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about.cy","base_path":"/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about.cy","content_id":"5f5a1d52-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","document_type":"about","links":{},"locale":"cy","public_updated_at":"2024-07-16T08:26:16Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"Amdanom ni","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about.cy","withdrawn":false},{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/ministry-of-justice/about","base_path":"/government/organis